draft_body:
Dear Joel Conway,

I hope you are doing well.

I am reaching out to express my interest in junior quantitative, model validation, risk, or quantitative research opportunities at Neuberger Berman.

I am a Toronto-based quantitative analyst with experience across model validation, asset allocation, and quantitative research in asset management, hedge fund, and academic environments. My background includes hands-on work in Python and R on stress testing, time-series modelling, volatility models, portfolio construction, and risk analytics. I have also worked on derivatives-related validation topics, macro regime analysis, and credit-risk-oriented research workflows. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

Most recently, I have been working on quantitative research and portfolio analytics projects, including trade reconstruction, synthetic NAV and PnL analysis, regime classification, and portfolio risk monitoring. Previously, I worked in model validation and asset allocation roles where I developed a Heston-Nandi GARCH validation model, a Merton-based stress-testing framework, and macro-regime allocation tools. :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}

Given your role as Quantitative Analyst, I thought it would be relevant to introduce myself directly. I would be very glad to share my background and discuss whether there may be a fit with your team or with broader quantitative, risk, or research functions at Neuberger Berman.

I am based in Toronto, hold a valid Canadian work permit, and am available immediately. My resume is attached for convenience. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}

Thank you very much for your time and consideration.

Best regards,

